The paper discusses the state of the art in solving real-world optimization problems using surrogate-based optimization and nature-inspired metaheuristics. These topics are closely related to the fields of neural networks (cs.NE), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and control systems (cs.SY). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
